<subSubSection pageId="133" pageNumber="134" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="133" pageNumber="134">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="133" pageNumber="134">
A rather variable plant, sometimes glabrous, sometimes densely adpressed pubescent so approaching 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowe, Ann. Mag. Nat. Hist., ser. 3,6: 155. 1860. (Lowe" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus caput-medusae" order="Solanales" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caput-medusae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">Convolvulus caput-medusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this respect; flowers can be solitary and pedunculate (e.g. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">Davis</emphasis>
48684), when the spine-like peduncles persist, but may also develop in apparent pedicellate clusters on virgate brachyblasts. These differences merit further study.
</paragraph>
